Type: Package
Package: LLMRcontent
Title: LLM-Assisted Content Analysis for the Social Sciences
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R:
    person("Ali", "Sanaei", , "sanaei@uchicago.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A validated workflow for content analysis with large language models,
    built on 'LLMR'. Three connected concerns, one package. Coding turns a
    codebook and a sealed gold standard into error-corrected category
    prevalences with reliability against held-out human labels. Robustness audits
    test whether a coded conclusion survives the measurement multiverse of
    prompts, models, label orders, and temperatures, reporting sign, rank, and
    fragility. Archives turn the audit log of a study into a content-addressed,
    sealed, reviewer-runnable replication record. The report() output for each
    object states its measurement-error, fragility, and verifiability stance: a
    coding result is a measurement with known error, an audit is a fragility
    statement, and an archive is a verifiable record, not a claim of truth. An
    optional Shiny GUI (run_content_studio()) drives the same workflow
    interactively.
